{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843320531,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d78828a3a001rcTae19fQj6bMb","messageID":"msg_d788273ba001BDMFCdVivEEk9Y","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a319cf15ad1c4c3c8f78fcd7483d6995","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 ŌĆö WorkloadManager HTTP µ£ŹÕŖĪµĪåµ×Č\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: Language: Go  \n5: Size: M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the HTTP service framework for WorkloadManager, providing RESTful API infrastructure, middleware architecture, lifecycle management, health endpoints, and unified error handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: HTTPServer Configuration\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** the `server.go` file defines the HTTP server core implementation  \n20: **WHEN** a developer needs to configure and manage the HTTP server lifecycle  \n21: **THEN** `HTTPServer` struct and `Config` struct shall be available with proper fields and methods\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: HTTPServer struct definition\n27: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/server.go\n28: WHEN reading the HTTPServer struct\n29: THEN it SHALL contain fields: server *http.Server, router chi.Router, config Config, handlers map[string]Handler, logger Logger, stopCh chan struct{}\n30: \n31: // Scenario 2: Config struct fields\n32: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/config.go\n33: WHEN reading the Config struct\n34: THEN it SHALL contain fields: Addr string, ReadTimeout time.Duration, WriteTimeout time.Duration, IdleTimeout time.Duration, ShutdownTimeout time.Duration, EnableHealthz bool, EnableReadyz bool\n35: \n36: // Scenario 3: DefaultConfig function\n37: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/config.go\n38: WHEN calling DefaultConfig()\n39: THEN it SHALL return Config with Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s, EnableHealthz true, EnableReadyz true\n40: \n41: // Scenario 4: HTTPServer constructor\n42: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/server.go\n43: WHEN calling NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger)\n44: THEN it SHALL return *HTTPServer with router initialized using chi.NewRouter()\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### REQ-002: HTTPServer Lifecycle Management\n50: \n51: **GIVEN** HTTPServer needs to support graceful startup and shutdown  \n52: **WHEN** managing the server lifecycle  \n53: **THEN** Start, Stop, and GracefulShutdown methods shall be properly implemented\n54: \n55: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: // Scenario 1: HTTPServer.Start method\n59: GIVEN an HTTPServer instance with valid config\n60: WHEN calling Start()\n61: THEN it SHALL configure http.Server with timeouts from Config\n62: AND it SHALL start ListenAndServe on the configured address\n63: AND it SHALL return error channel for async error handling\n64: \n65: // Scenario 2: HTTPServer.Stop method\n66: GIVEN a running HTTPServer instance\n67: WHEN calling Stop(ctx context.Context)\n68: THEN it SHALL call http.Server.Shutdown(ctx)\n69: AND it SHALL wait for existing connections to complete within ShutdownTimeout\n70: AND it SHALL close stopCh to signal shutdown complete\n71: \n72: // Scenario 3: HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown method\n73: GIVEN a running HTTPServer instance\n74: WHEN calling GracefulShutdown()\n75: THEN it SHALL setup signal handler for SIGTERM and SIGINT\n76: AND it SHALL call Stop() on signal receipt\n77: \n78: // Scenario 4: Graceful shutdown with context timeout\n79: GIVEN an HTTPServer with ShutdownTimeout 30s\n80: WHEN graceful shutdown is triggered\n81: THEN existing connections SHALL complete within 30 seconds\n82: AND new connections SHALL be rejected after shutdown starts\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### REQ-003: Router Implementation\n88: \n89: **GIVEN** the router needs to support route grouping and middleware scoping  \n90: **WHEN** configuring RESTful API routes  \n91: **THEN** Router struct wrapping chi.Router shall be properly defined\n92: \n93: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n94: \n95: ```go\n96: // Scenario 1: Router struct definition\n97: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/router.go\n98: WHEN reading the Router struct\n99: THEN it SHALL embed chi.Router\n100: \n101: // Scenario 2: NewRouter constructor\n102: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/router.go\n103: WHEN calling NewRouter()\n104: THEN it SHALL return *Router with chi.NewRouter() initialized\n105: \n106: // Scenario 3: RegisterHandlers method\n107: GIVEN a Router instance and multiple Handler implementations\n108: WHEN calling RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler)\n109: THEN each handler's Register method SHALL be called on the underlying chi.Router\n110: \n111: // Scenario 4: chi router dependency\n112: GIVEN go.mod\n113: WHEN reading dependencies\n114: THEN github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 SHALL be listed as a dependency\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### REQ-004: Handler Interface\n120: \n121: **GIVEN** handlers need a common registration interface  \n122: **WHEN** implementing new API endpoint handlers  \n123: **THEN** Handler interface and HandlerFunc type shall be properly defined\n124: \n125: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n126: \n127: ```go\n128: // Scenario 1: Handler interface definition\n129: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go\n130: WHEN reading the Handler interface\n131: THEN it SHALL define Register(r chi.Router) method\n132: \n133: // Scenario 2: HandlerFunc type definition\n134: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go\n135: WHEN reading the HandlerFunc type\n136: THEN it SHALL be defined as type HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n137: \n138: // Scenario 3: HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP implementation\n139: GIVEN a HandlerFunc instance\n140: WHEN calling ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n141: THEN it SHALL call the HandlerFunc and handle errors via HandleError\n142: \n143: // Scenario 4: RegisterHandler method on HTTPServer\n144: GIVEN an HTTPServer instance\n145: WHEN calling RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler)\n146: THEN the handler SHALL be stored in handlers map\n147: AND it SHALL be registered on the router\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### REQ-005: Health Handler Implementation\n153: \n154: **GIVEN** Kubernetes needs liveness and readiness probe endpoints  \n155: **WHEN** implementing health check endpoints  \n156: **THEN** HealthHandler with /healthz and /readyz shall be properly implemented\n157: \n158: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: // Scenario 1: HealthHandler struct definition\n162: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go\n163: WHEN reading the HealthHandler struct\n164: THEN it SHALL contain checker HealthChecker field\n165: \n166: // Scenario 2: HealthChecker interface definition\n167: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go\n168: WHEN reading the HealthChecker interface\n169: THEN it SHALL define IsHealthy() bool and IsReady() bool methods\n170: \n171: // Scenario 3: NewHealthHandler constructor\n172: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go\n173: WHEN calling NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker)\n174: THEN it SHALL return *HealthHandler with checker field set\n175: \n176: // Scenario 4: healthz endpoint\n177: GIVEN a HealthHandler registered on router\n178: WHEN GET request is sent to /healthz\n179: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON body {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n180: \n181: // Scenario 5: readyz endpoint with checker ready\n182: GIVEN a HealthHandler with checker where IsReady() returns true\n183: WHEN GET request is sent to /readyz\n184: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON body {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n185: \n186: // Scenario 6: readyz endpoint with checker not ready\n187: GIVEN a HealthHandler with checker where IsReady() returns false\n188: WHEN GET request is sent to /readyz\n189: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with JSON body {\"status\": \"not ready\"}\n190: \n191: // Scenario 7: readyz endpoint without checker\n192: GIVEN a HealthHandler with nil checker\n193: WHEN GET request is sent to /readyz\n194: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with JSON body {\"status\": \"not ready\"}\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### REQ-006: Logging Middleware\n200: \n201: **GIVEN** requests need structured logging  \n202: **WHEN** implementing request logging middleware  \n203: **THEN** LoggingMiddleware shall capture request details and response status\n204: \n205: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n206: \n207: ```go\n208: // Scenario 1: LoggingMiddleware struct definition\n209: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go\n210: WHEN reading the LoggingMiddleware struct\n211: THEN it SHALL contain logger Logger field\n212: \n213: // Scenario 2: NewLoggingMiddleware constructor\n214: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go\n215: WHEN calling NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger)\n216: THEN it SHALL return *LoggingMiddleware with logger field set\n217: \n218: // Scenario 3: Wrap method signature\n219: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go\n220: WHEN reading the Wrap method\n221: THEN it SHALL have signature func(m *LoggingMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n222: \n223: // Scenario 4: Request logging fields\n224: GIVEN LoggingMiddleware wrapping a handler\n225: WHEN a request is processed\n226: THEN logger SHALL log: method, path, status, duration\n227: \n228: // Scenario 5: responseWriterWrapper captures status\n229: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go\n230: WHEN reading responseWriterWrapper struct\n231: THEN it SHALL embed http.ResponseWriter and capture status code field\n232: \n233: // Scenario 6: responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader\n234: GIVEN a responseWriterWrapper instance\n235: WHEN WriteHeader(code int) is called\n236: THEN status field SHALL be set to code\n237: AND embedded ResponseWriter.WriteHeader SHALL be called\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### REQ-007: Recovery Middleware\n243: \n244: **GIVEN** panics in handlers need to be recovered  \n245: **WHEN** implementing panic recovery middleware  \n246: **THEN** RecoveryMiddleware shall catch panics and return 500 response\n247: \n248: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: // Scenario 1: RecoveryMiddleware struct definition\n252: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go\n253: WHEN reading the RecoveryMiddleware struct\n254: THEN it SHALL contain logger Logger field\n255: \n256: // Scenario 2: NewRecoveryMiddleware constructor\n257: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go\n258: WHEN calling NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger)\n259: THEN it SHALL return *RecoveryMiddleware with logger field set\n260: \n261: // Scenario 3: Wrap method catches panic\n262: GIVEN RecoveryMiddleware wrapping a handler that panics\n263: WHEN the handler panics\n264: THEN panic SHALL be recovered\n265: AND logger SHALL log error with panic value and path\n266: AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with body \"Internal Server Error\"\n267: \n268: // Scenario 4: Normal request passes through\n269: GIVEN RecoveryMiddleware wrapping a normal handler\n270: WHEN the handler does not panic\n271: THEN request SHALL pass through normally\n272: AND response SHALL be from the wrapped handler\n273: ```\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ### REQ-008: CORS Middleware\n278: \n279: **GIVEN** cross-origin requests need CORS headers  \n280: **WHEN** implementing CORS middleware  \n281: **THEN** CORSMiddleware shall add appropriate CORS headers and handle preflight\n282: \n283: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n284: \n285: ```go\n286: // Scenario 1: CORSMiddleware struct definition\n287: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go\n288: WHEN reading the CORSMiddleware struct\n289: THEN it SHALL contain config fields for allowed origins, methods, headers\n290: \n291: // Scenario 2: CORS headers added to response\n292: GIVEN CORSMiddleware wrapping a handler\n293: WHEN a request is processed\n294: THEN response SHALL include Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n295: \n296: // Scenario 3: Preflight OPTIONS request\n297: GIVEN CORSMiddleware wrapping a handler\n298: WHEN OPTIONS request is sent\n299: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with CORS preflight headers\n300: AND Access-Control-Allow-Methods header SHALL be present\n301: AND Access-Control-Allow-Headers header SHALL be present\n302: \n303: // Scenario 4: NewCORSMiddleware constructor\n304: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go\n305: WHEN calling NewCORSMiddleware with allowed origins and methods\n306: THEN it SHALL return *CORSMiddleware with config fields set\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### REQ-009: Request/Response Data Structures\n312: \n313: **GIVEN** API responses need unified JSON format  \n314: **WHEN** defining response data structures  \n315: **THEN** ErrorResponse and SuccessResponse shall be properly defined\n316: \n317: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n318: \n319: ```go\n320: // Scenario 1: ErrorResponse struct definition\n321: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/types.go\n322: WHEN reading the ErrorResponse struct\n323: THEN it SHALL contain fields: Code string with JSON tag \"code\", Message string with JSON tag \"message\", Details any with JSON tag \"details,omitempty\"\n324: \n325: // Scenario 2: SuccessResponse struct definition\n326: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/types.go\n327: WHEN reading the SuccessResponse struct\n328: THEN it SHALL contain field: Data any with JSON tag \"data\"\n329: \n330: // Scenario 3: ErrorResponse JSON serialization\n331: GIVEN an ErrorResponse with Code \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", Message \"Invalid parameter\", Details map[string]string{\"field\": \"name\"}\n332: WHEN marshaling to JSON\n333: THEN output SHALL be {\"code\":\"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\"message\":\"Invalid parameter\",\"details\":{\"field\":\"name\"}}\n334: \n335: // Scenario 4: SuccessResponse JSON serialization\n336: GIVEN a SuccessResponse with Data containing a map\n337: WHEN marshaling to JSON\n338: THEN output SHALL contain \"data\" key with the nested data\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### REQ-010: Unified Error Handling\n344: \n345: **GIVEN** errors need unified HTTP response format  \n346: **WHEN** handling errors in handlers  \n347: **THEN** HandleError function shall map errors to correct HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n348: \n349: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n350: \n351: ```go\n352: // Scenario 1: HandleError function signature\n353: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/types.go\n354: WHEN reading HandleError function\n355: THEN it SHALL have signature func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error)\n356: \n357: // Scenario 2: Validation error response\n358: GIVEN HandleError called with validation error\n359: WHEN the error indicates invalid request\n360: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 400 with ErrorResponse Code \"VALIDATION_ERROR\"\n361: \n362: // Scenario 3: Not found error response\n363: GIVEN HandleError called with not found error\n364: WHEN the error indicates resource not found\n365: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 404 with ErrorResponse Code \"NOT_FOUND\"\n366: \n367: // Scenario 4: Internal error response\n368: GIVEN HandleError called with internal error\n369: WHEN the error is unexpected\n370: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 500 with ErrorResponse Code \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"\n371: \n372: // Scenario 5: Service unavailable error response\n373: GIVEN HandleError called with service unavailable error\n374: WHEN the error indicates dependency unavailable\n375: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with ErrorResponse Code \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"\n376: \n377: // Scenario 6: ErrorResponse sets Content-Type\n378: GIVEN HandleError writes ErrorResponse\n379: WHEN writing response\n380: THEN Content-Type header SHALL be \"application/json\"\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ### REQ-011: Middleware Chain Order\n386: \n387: **GIVEN** middleware needs to execute in correct order  \n388: **WHEN** configuring middleware on the router  \n389: **THEN** middleware shall execute in the order: Recovery ŌåÆ Logging ŌåÆ CORS ŌåÆ Handler\n390: \n391: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n392: \n393: ```go\n394: // Scenario 1: Recovery executes first\n395: GIVEN middleware chain Recovery ŌåÆ Logging ŌåÆ Handler that panics\n396: WHEN handler panics\n397: THEN Recovery middleware SHALL catch panic before Logging logs\n398: \n399: // Scenario 2: Logging captures request duration\n400: GIVEN middleware chain Recovery ŌåÆ Logging ŌåÆ Handler\n401: WHEN request is processed\n402: THEN Logging SHALL capture full request duration including handler execution\n403: \n404: // Scenario 3: Middleware setup method\n405: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/server.go\n406: WHEN reading setupMiddleware method\n407: THEN it SHALL apply middleware in correct order using chi.Use()\n408: \n409: // Scenario 4: CORS middleware optional\n410: GIVEN middleware configuration\n411: WHEN CORS middleware is not configured\n412: THEN CORS middleware SHALL NOT be applied to the chain\n413: ```\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ### REQ-012: Logger Interface\n418: \n419: **GIVEN** the server needs structured logging  \n420: **WHEN** defining logger abstraction  \n421: **THEN** Logger interface shall support Info and Error methods\n422: \n423: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n424: \n425: ```go\n426: // Scenario 1: Logger interface definition\n427: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/types.go\n428: WHEN reading the Logger interface\n429: THEN it SHALL define Info(msg string, args ...any) method\n430: AND it SHALL define Error(msg string, args ...any) method\n431: \n432: // Scenario 2: Logger usage in HTTPServer\n433: GIVEN an HTTPServer instance\n434: WHEN logging events\n435: THEN logger.Info and logger.Error SHALL be used for structured logging\n436: \n437: // Scenario 3: Logger usage in middleware\n438: GIVEN LoggingMiddleware and RecoveryMiddleware\n439: WHEN logging request details or panics\n440: THEN logger SHALL be used for all log output\n441: ```\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ### REQ-013: Directory Structure\n446: \n447: **GIVEN** the module needs proper package structure  \n448: **WHEN** organizing code files  \n449: **THEN** files shall be organized according to the defined structure\n450: \n451: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: // Scenario 1: Main package files\n455: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/\n456: WHEN listing files\n457: THEN server.go, router.go, config.go, types.go SHALL exist\n458: \n459: // Scenario 2: Handlers directory\n460: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/\n461: WHEN listing files\n462: THEN handler.go and health.go SHALL exist\n463: \n464: // Scenario 3: Middleware directory\n465: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/\n466: WHEN listing files\n467: THEN logging.go, recovery.go, cors.go SHALL exist\n468: \n469: // Scenario 4: Package documentation\n470: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go\n471: WHEN reading the file\n472: THEN package-level godoc comment SHALL be present\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ### REQ-014: Unit Tests\n478: \n479: **GIVEN** the implementation needs test coverage  \n480: **WHEN** verifying functionality  \n481: **THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n482: \n483: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n484: \n485: ```go\n486: // Scenario 1: Types tests\n487: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go\n488: WHEN running tests\n489: THEN HandleError tests SHALL verify correct JSON format and status codes\n490: AND SuccessResponse tests SHALL verify correct marshaling\n491: \n492: // Scenario 2: Server tests\n493: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\n494: WHEN running tests\n495: THEN NewHTTPServer tests SHALL verify default config\n496: AND Start/Stop tests SHALL verify lifecycle\n497: AND graceful shutdown tests SHALL verify context timeout handling\n498: \n499: // Scenario 3: Router tests\n500: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go\n501: WHEN running tests\n502: THEN NewRouter tests SHALL verify router initialization\n503: AND RegisterHandlers tests SHALL verify multiple handler registration\n504: \n505: // Scenario 4: Health handler tests\n506: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go\n507: WHEN running tests\n508: THEN healthz test SHALL verify HTTP 200 with {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n509: AND readyz tests SHALL verify HTTP 200/503 based on IsReady()\n510: \n511: // Scenario 5: Logging middleware tests\n512: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go\n513: WHEN running tests\n514: THEN tests SHALL verify request method, path, status captured\n515: AND responseWriterWrapper tests SHALL verify status code capture\n516: \n517: // Scenario 6: Recovery middleware tests\n518: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go\n519: WHEN running tests\n520: THEN tests SHALL verify panic recovery\n521: AND tests SHALL verify HTTP 500 on panic\n522: \n523: // Scenario 7: CORS middleware tests\n524: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go\n525: WHEN running tests\n526: THEN tests SHALL verify Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n527: AND tests SHALL verify OPTIONS preflight handling\n528: ```\n529: \n530: ---\n531: \n532: ### REQ-015: Integration Tests\n533: \n534: **GIVEN** the server needs end-to-end verification  \n535: **WHEN** testing with real HTTP requests  \n536: **THEN** integration tests shall verify complete request flow\n537: \n538: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: // Scenario 1: End-to-end health check\n542: GIVEN a running HTTPServer on random port\n543: WHEN GET request sent to /healthz\n544: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with correct JSON body\n545: \n546: // Scenario 2: End-to-end readiness check\n547: GIVEN a running HTTPServer on random port\n548: WHEN GET request sent to /readyz\n549: THEN response SHALL match HealthChecker state\n550: \n551: // Scenario 3: Middleware chain verification\n552: GIVEN a running HTTPServer with full middleware chain\n553: WHEN request is sent\n554: THEN middleware SHALL execute in correct order\n555: AND logging SHALL capture request details\n556: \n557: // Scenario 4: Panic recovery in integration\n558: GIVEN a running HTTPServer with endpoint that panics\n559: WHEN request is sent to panicking endpoint\n560: THEN server SHALL NOT crash\n561: AND response SHALL be HTTP 500\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ---\n565: \n566: ### REQ-016: Code Quality\n567: \n568: **GIVEN** the code needs to meet quality standards  \n569: **WHEN** running linting and validation  \n570: **THEN** code shall pass go vet and golangci-lint\n571: \n572: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n573: \n574: ```go\n575: // Scenario 1: go vet passes\n576: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/\n577: WHEN running go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n578: THEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n579: \n580: // Scenario 2: golangci-lint passes\n581: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/\n582: WHEN running golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n583: THEN zero linting issues SHALL be reported\n584: \n585: // Scenario 3: Build succeeds\n586: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/\n587: WHEN running go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n588: THEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n589: \n590: // Scenario 4: Test coverage threshold\n591: GIVEN pkg/workloadmanager/\n592: WHEN running go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n593: THEN coverage SHALL be greater than 80%\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Implementation Files\n599: \n600: | File | Purpose |\n601: |------|---------|\n602: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTPServer implementation with lifecycle management |\n603: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | Router struct wrapping chi.Router |\n604: | `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` | Config struct and DefaultConfig function |\n605: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | ErrorResponse, SuccessResponse, HandleError, Logger interface |\n606: | `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go` | Package-level documentation |\n607: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go` | Handler interface and HandlerFunc type |\n608: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | HealthHandler and HealthChecker interface |\n609: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | LoggingMiddleware and responseWriterWrapper |\n610: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | RecoveryMiddleware |\n611: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORSMiddleware |\n612: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` | HTTPServer unit tests |\n613: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go` | Router unit tests |\n614: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` | Types and HandleError unit tests |\n615: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` | HealthHandler unit tests |\n616: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go` | LoggingMiddleware unit tests |\n617: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go` | RecoveryMiddleware unit tests |\n618: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go` | CORSMiddleware unit tests |\n619: | `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` | End-to-end integration tests |\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## Dependencies\n624: \n625: | Package | Purpose |\n626: |---------|---------|\n627: | `net/http` | Standard library HTTP server |\n628: | `context` | Request context for graceful shutdown |\n629: | `sync` | Concurrency control |\n630: | `os/signal` | Signal handling for graceful shutdown |\n631: | `time` | Timeout configuration |\n632: | `encoding/json` | JSON serialization for responses |\n633: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | Lightweight HTTP router |\n634: \n635: ---\n636: \n637: ## API Endpoints\n638: \n639: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n640: |----------|--------|---------|\n641: | `/healthz` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe |\n642: | `/readyz` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe |\n643: \n644: ---\n645: \n646: ## Error Codes\n647: \n648: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n649: |------|-------------|-------------|\n650: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Invalid request parameter |\n651: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Resource not found |\n652: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Unexpected server error |\n653: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Dependency unavailable |\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## Validation Checklist\n658: \n659: - [ ] HTTPServer supports graceful startup and shutdown\n660: - [ ] Router framework supports route grouping with chi\n661: - [ ] Middleware chain executes in correct order\n662: - [ ] Health endpoints `/healthz` and `/readyz` respond correctly\n663: - [ ] Error responses use unified JSON format\n664: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n665: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n666: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n667: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n668: - [ ] All exported types have godoc comments\n\n(End of file - total 668 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 ŌĆö WorkloadManager HTTP µ£ŹÕŖĪµĪåµ×Č\n\nModule: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \nLanguage: Go  \nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP service framework for WorkloadManager, providing RESTful API infrastructure, middleware architecture, lifecycle management, health endpoints, and unified error handling.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: HTTPServer Configuration\n\n**GIVEN** the `server.go` file defines the HTTP server core implementation  \n**WHEN** a developer needs to configure and manage the HTTP server lifecycle  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843320488,"end":1775843320529}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843320537,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d7882937d001I0QSVqXUalZRZf","messageID":"msg_d788273ba001BDMFCdVivEEk9Y","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9b2dcc1467c74422b138749db523c023","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-001 ŌĆö CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n22:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `SchemeGroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Group version kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** the `addKnownTypes` function is invoked\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL register `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `CodeInterpreter`, and `CodeInterpreterList` with the scheme\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type definition\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime struct shape\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n43: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntime` struct definition\n44: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec AgentRuntimeSpec` and `Status AgentRuntimeStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeList struct shape\n47: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n48: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeList` struct definition\n49: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []AgentRuntime` with JSON tag `items`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: CRD markers on AgentRuntime\n52: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n53: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n54: - **THEN** the `AgentRuntime` type SHALL have:\n55:   - `+genclient` marker\n56:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n57:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n58:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec definition\n63: \n64: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with required fields for session management and pod templating.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec fields\n67: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n68: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct\n69: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n70:   - `MaxSessionDuration string` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration`\n71:   - `SessionTimeout string` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout`\n72:   - `TargetPort []TargetPort` with JSON tag `targetPort`\n73:   - `PodTemplate PodTemplateSpec` with JSON tag `podTemplate`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec required fields\n76: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n77: - **WHEN** examining the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct markers\n78: - **THEN** the struct SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` or equivalent kubebuilder markers for `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate` fields\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n81: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n82: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n86: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n87: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### Requirement: TargetPort type definition\n93: \n94: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` to specify how traffic is routed to the agent runtime pod.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: TargetPort struct fields\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** reading the `TargetPort` struct\n99: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n100:   - `Port int32` with JSON tag `port` (required)\n101:   - `Protocol ProtocolType` with JSON tag `protocol` (enum: HTTP, HTTPS)\n102:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional)\n103:   - `PathPrefix string` with JSON tag `pathPrefix` (optional)\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: ProtocolType enum definition\n106: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n107: - **WHEN** reading the `ProtocolType` type definition\n108: - **THEN** it SHALL be a string type with `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS` marker and constants `ProtocolHTTP` and `ProtocolHTTPS`\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus definition\n113: \n114: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with standard Kubernetes condition fields.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeStatus fields\n117: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n118: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct\n119: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n122: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n123: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n125:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Optional` marker\n126:   - `+listType=map` marker\n127:   - `+listMapKey=type` marker\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n132: \n133: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntime\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n137: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n138: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntime) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntime)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields including `Spec.TargetPort` slice\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeList\n141: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n142: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n143: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeList) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeSpec\n146: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n147: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n148: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeSpec)` SHALL exist\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for TargetPort\n151: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n152: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n153: - **THEN** `func (in *TargetPort) DeepCopyInto(out *TargetPort)` SHALL exist\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeStatus\n156: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n157: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n158: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeStatus)` SHALL exist\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: CRD generation\n163: \n164: The system SHALL generate CRD YAML that matches the expected schema from `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`.\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: CRD generation command\n167: - **GIVEN** the repository with types defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n168: - **WHEN** running `make gen-crd`\n169: - **THEN** the command SHALL invoke `controller-gen crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... output:dir=manifests/charts/base/crds`\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Generated CRD metadata\n172: - **GIVEN** the generated `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n173: - **WHEN** examining the CRD\n174: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n175: - AND `spec.group` SHALL be `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n176: - AND `spec.names.kind` SHALL be `AgentRuntime`\n177: - AND `spec.names.plural` SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n178: - AND `spec.scope` SHALL be `Namespaced`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Generated CRD version\n181: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n182: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions`\n183: - **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one version with `name: v1alpha1`, `served: true`, and `storage: true`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Generated CRD spec schema\n186: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n187: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0].schema.openAPIV3Schema.properties.spec`\n188: - **THEN** the `required` array SHALL include `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate`\n189: - AND `properties.maxSessionDuration.default` SHALL be `\"8h\"`\n190: - AND `properties.sessionTimeout.default` SHALL be `\"15m\"`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Generated CRD status subresource\n193: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n194: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0]`\n195: - **THEN** `subresources.status` SHALL be present\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n200: \n201: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Group version registration for client-gen\n204: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n205: - **WHEN** reading the file\n206: - **THEN** `SchemeBuilder` SHALL be defined using `NewSchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` SHALL be exposed as `localSchemeBuilder.AddToScheme(scheme)`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Types implement runtime.Object\n209: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n210: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n211: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Client generation command\n214: - **GIVEN** types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n215: - **WHEN** running `make gen-client`\n216: - **THEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh` SHALL be invoked, which runs `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with:\n217:   - `--with-watch` flag\n218:   - `--output-dir client-go`\n219:   - `--output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n220:   - Input API at `runtime/v1alpha1`\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Generated typed client exists\n223: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n224: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n225: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Generated informer exists\n228: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n229: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n230: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Generated lister exists\n233: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n234: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n235: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `AgentRuntimes(namespace string)` methods\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-001 ŌĆö CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843320496,"end":1775843320535}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843320540,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d78829db5001Z5x4DEY67ze6km","messageID":"msg_d788273ba001BDMFCdVivEEk9Y","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e380ca8af7114d60b436e161c13a1337","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"encoding/json\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"net/http\"\n7: \n8: \t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n9: )\n10: \n11: // Handler defines the interface for registering routes on a chi router.\n12: type Handler interface {\n13: \tRegister(r chi.Router)\n14: }\n15: \n16: // Logger defines the interface for logging within the workloadmanager package.\n17: type Logger interface {\n18: \tInfo(msg string, args ...any)\n19: \tError(msg string, args ...any)\n20: }\n21: \n22: // ErrorResponse represents a standardized API error response.\n23: type ErrorResponse struct {\n24: \tCode    string `json:\"code\"`\n25: \tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n26: \tDetails any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n27: }\n28: \n29: // SuccessResponse represents a standardized API success response.\n30: type SuccessResponse struct {\n31: \tData any `json:\"data\"`\n32: }\n33: \n34: // ValidationError indicates invalid request parameters.\n35: type ValidationError struct {\n36: \tField  string\n37: \tReason string\n38: }\n39: \n40: func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n41: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n42: }\n43: \n44: // NotFoundError indicates a requested resource was not found.\n45: type NotFoundError struct {\n46: \tResource string\n47: \tName     string\n48: }\n49: \n50: func (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n51: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n52: }\n53: \n54: // InternalError indicates an unexpected server error occurred.\n55: type InternalError struct {\n56: \tErr error\n57: }\n58: \n59: func (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n60: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n61: }\n62: \n63: // ServiceUnavailableError indicates a dependency service is unavailable.\n64: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n65: \tDependency string\n66: }\n67: \n68: func (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n69: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n70: }\n71: \n72: // HandleError maps error types to appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses.\n73: // It always sets Content-Type: application/json header.\n74: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n75: \tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n76: \n77: \tvar resp ErrorResponse\n78: \tvar status int\n79: \n80: \tswitch e := err.(type) {\n81: \tcase *ValidationError:\n82: \t\tstatus = http.StatusBadRequest\n83: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n84: \t\t\tCode:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n85: \t\t\tMessage: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n86: \t\t\tDetails: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n87: \t\t}\n88: \tcase *NotFoundError:\n89: \t\tstatus = http.StatusNotFound\n90: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n91: \t\t\tCode:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n92: \t\t\tMessage: e.Error(),\n93: \t\t}\n94: \tcase *ServiceUnavailableError:\n95: \t\tstatus = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n96: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n97: \t\t\tCode:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n98: \t\t\tMessage: e.Error(),\n99: \t\t}\n100: \tcase *InternalError:\n101: \t\tstatus = http.StatusInternalServerError\n102: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n103: \t\t\tCode:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n104: \t\t\tMessage: \"Unexpected server error\",\n105: \t\t}\n106: \tdefault:\n107: \t\tstatus = http.StatusInternalServerError\n108: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n109: \t\t\tCode:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n110: \t\t\tMessage: \"Unexpected server error\",\n111: \t\t}\n112: \t}\n113: \n114: \tw.WriteHeader(status)\n115: \tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n116: }\n\n(End of file - total 116 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n)\n\n// Handler defines the interface for registering routes on a chi router.\ntype Handler interface {\n\tRegister(r chi.Router)\n}\n\n// Logger defines the interface for logging within the workloadmanager package.\ntype Logger interface {\n\tInfo(msg string, args ...any)\n\tError(msg string, args ...any)\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go","time":{"start":1775843320502,"end":1775843320538}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843320542,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d78828f2e001WZRvLys1SIEtS4","messageID":"msg_d788273ba001BDMFCdVivEEk9Y","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-95559cde4cff442788b678d578a10354","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-002 ŌĆö CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n22:   - `shared_types.go` with `AuthModeType` enum and `TargetPort` type\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** reading the file\n33: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n34: - AND `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL be `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`\n35: - AND `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL be `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type definition\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter struct shape\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n45: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreter` struct definition\n46: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec CodeInterpreterSpec` and `Status CodeInterpreterStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterList struct shape\n49: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n50: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterList` struct definition\n51: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []CodeInterpreter` with JSON tag `items`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: CRD markers on CodeInterpreter\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n55: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n56: - **THEN** the `CodeInterpreter` type SHALL have:\n57:   - `+genclient` marker\n58:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n59:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n60:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n61:   - `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced` marker\n62:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` marker\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec definition\n67: \n68: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with fields for sandbox template, session management, warm pool, and authentication.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n72: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct\n73: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n74:   - `Ports []TargetPort` with JSON tag `ports` (optional)\n75:   - `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` with JSON tag `template` (required)\n76:   - `SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout` (optional, default 15m)\n77:   - `MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration` (optional, default 8h)\n78:   - `WarmPoolSize *int32` with JSON tag `warmPoolSize` (optional)\n79:   - `AuthMode AuthModeType` with JSON tag `authMode` (optional, default picod)\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Template field is required\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n83: - **WHEN** examining the `Template` field markers\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` marker\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n87: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n88: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n93: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: AuthMode enum and default\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** examining the `AuthMode` field marker\n99: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n100:   - `+kubebuilder:default=picod` marker\n101:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none` marker\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate definition\n106: \n107: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` for configuring code interpreter pods.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate fields\n110: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n111: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` struct\n112: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n113:   - `Labels map[string]string` with JSON tag `labels` (optional)\n114:   - `Annotations map[string]string` with JSON tag `annotations` (optional)\n115:   - `RuntimeClassName *string` with JSON tag `runtimeClassName` (optional)\n116:   - `Image string` with JSON tag `image` (optional)\n117:   - `ImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy` with JSON tag `imagePullPolicy` (optional)\n118:   - `ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference` with JSON tag `imagePullSecrets` (optional)\n119:   - `Environment []corev1.EnvVar` with JSON tag `environment` (optional)\n120:   - `Command []string` with JSON tag `command` (optional)\n121:   - `Args []string` with JSON tag `args` (optional)\n122:   - `Resources corev1.ResourceRequirements` with JSON tag `resources` (optional)\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets list markers\n125: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n126: - **WHEN** examining the `ImagePullSecrets` field\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n128:   - `+patchMergeKey=name` marker\n129:   - `+patchStrategy=merge` marker\n130:   - `+listType=map` marker\n131:   - `+listMapKey=name` marker\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus definition\n136: \n137: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with conditions and readiness flag.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n140: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n141: - **WHEN** reading the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct\n142: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n143:   - `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions` (optional)\n144:   - `Ready bool` with JSON tag `ready` (optional)\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n147: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n148: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n150:   - `+optional` marker\n151:   - `+listType=atomic` marker\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: AuthModeType enum definition\n156: \n157: The system SHALL define `AuthModeType` in `shared_types.go` as an enum for authentication modes.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AuthModeType type definition\n160: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n161: - **WHEN** reading the file\n162: - **THEN** `AuthModeType` SHALL be defined as `type AuthModeType string`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthModeType constants\n165: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n166: - **WHEN** reading the file\n167: - **THEN** the following constants SHALL be defined:\n168:   - `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"`\n169:   - `AuthModeNone AuthModeType = \"none\"`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n174: \n175: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreter\n178: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n179: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n180: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreter) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreter)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterList\n183: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n184: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n185: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterList) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSpec\n188: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n189: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n190: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSpec)` SHALL exist and correctly copy pointer fields including `Template`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`, and `WarmPoolSize`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n193: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n194: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n195: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate)` SHALL exist\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for CodeInterpreterStatus\n198: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n199: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n200: - **THEN** `func (in *CodeInterpreterStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *CodeInterpreterStatus)` SHALL exist\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: DeepCopyObject implementation\n203: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n204: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n205: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n210: \n211: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers for CodeInterpreter.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n214: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n215: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n216: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n219: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n220: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n221: - **THEN** `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` SHALL include `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Generated informer for CodeInterpreter\n224: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n225: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n226: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Generated lister for CodeInterpreter\n229: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n230: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n231: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `CodeInterpreters(namespace string)` methods\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: REST resource plural\n234: - **GIVEN** the generated typed client for CodeInterpreter\n235: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n236: - **THEN** the REST resource plural SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: JSON serialization\n241: \n242: The system SHALL ensure all types serialize correctly to/from JSON with camelCase field names.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON serialization\n245: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance with all fields populated\n246: - **WHEN** serializing to JSON\n247: - **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase field names: `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, `warmPoolSize`, `authMode`, `pathPrefix`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter JSON deserialization\n250: - **GIVEN** a JSON document with camelCase field names\n251: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreter`\n252: - **THEN** all fields SHALL be correctly populated including nested `Template` and `Ports` slice\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Default values applied on deserialization\n255: - **GIVEN** a JSON document without `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`, and `authMode` fields\n256: - **WHEN** deserializing to `CodeInterpreterSpec` with defaulting enabled\n257: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` SHALL default to `15m`\n258: - AND `MaxSessionDuration` SHALL default to `8h`\n259: - AND `AuthMode` SHALL default to `picod`\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: List type markers\n264: \n265: The system SHALL use correct Kubernetes list type markers for slice fields.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Ports list type\n268: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n269: - **WHEN** examining the `Ports` field in `CodeInterpreterSpec`\n270: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Conditions list type\n273: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n274: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field in `CodeInterpreterStatus`\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Environment list type\n278: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n279: - **WHEN** examining the `Environment` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Command list type\n283: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n284: - **WHEN** examining the `Command` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n285: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Args list type\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n289: - **WHEN** examining the `Args` field in `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+listType=atomic` marker\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-002 ŌĆö CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843320493,"end":1775843320540}}}}
