{"type":"text","timestamp":1775843462358,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d7882e9b2001bV3Xjxk4fhNso3","messageID":"msg_d7882d333001eRuGFZPJYNN3w0","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the delta-spec.md. Let me create it with proper GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios.","time":{"start":1775843462350,"end":1775843462350}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843462424,"sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","part":{"id":"prt_d7884ccd3001Js3KVDJGDzfm0c","messageID":"msg_d7882d333001eRuGFZPJYNN3w0","sessionID":"ses_2877dd2f3ffengL567zP5fRMrh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ef01a4e2b28941ae8c305c5faf67041e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 ŌĆö Sandbox ÕłøÕ╗║ÕżäńÉåÕÖ©\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxHandler struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `SandboxHandler` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n  - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n  - `namespace string` for default namespace\n\n#### Scenario: NewSandboxHandler constructor\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewSandboxHandler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, logger Logger, namespace string)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*SandboxHandler` with all fields initialized\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Handler registration interface\n\nThe system SHALL implement `Handler` interface for route registration.\n\n#### Scenario: Handler interface implementation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** examining `SandboxHandler`\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method from `workloadmanager.Handler` interface\n\n#### Scenario: Register method routes\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxHandler` instance\n- **WHEN** calling `Register(r chi.Router)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL register the following routes:\n  - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox creation\n  - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox retrieval\n  - `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox deletion\n  - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox listing\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CreateSandboxRequest type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define request types for sandbox creation API.\n\n#### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `CreateSandboxRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (required)\n  - `RuntimeName string` with JSON tag `runtimeName` (required)\n  - `RuntimeKind string` with JSON tag `runtimeKind` (required, enum: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n  - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId` (optional)\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeKind validation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** examining the `RuntimeKind` field\n- **THEN** valid values SHALL be `\"AgentRuntime\"` and `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: SandboxResponse type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define response types for sandbox API.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `SandboxResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Name string` with JSON tag `name`\n  - `PodName string` with JSON tag `podName`\n  - `Namespace string` with JSON tag `namespace`\n  - `Status string` with JSON tag `status`\n  - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId`\n  - `CreatedAt time.Time` with JSON tag `createdAt`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxListResponse struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `SandboxListResponse` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain field `Items []SandboxResponse` with JSON tag `items`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox creation logic\n\nThe system SHALL create Kubernetes Pods based on AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter templates.\n\n#### Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime spec\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n- **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the AgentRuntime\n\n#### Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter spec\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n- **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n- **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the CodeInterpreter\n\n#### Scenario: Pod creation from AgentRuntime template\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime spec with `Template *SandboxTemplate`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- AND the Pod's `Spec` SHALL be derived from `AgentRuntime.Spec.Template.Spec`\n\n#### Scenario: Pod creation from CodeInterpreter template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter spec with `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- AND the Pod's container image SHALL be from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template.Image`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Label application\n\nThe system SHALL apply required labels to sandbox pods according to shared_types.go constants.\n\n#### Scenario: Owner runtime label\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n- **WHEN** applying labels\n- **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` SHALL be set to the runtime name\n\n#### Scenario: Owner kind label\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n- **WHEN** applying labels\n- **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` SHALL be set to `RuntimeKind` value\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox type label for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** applying labels\n- **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"agent\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox type label for CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** applying labels\n- **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"code-interpreter\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID label\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created with `SessionID`\n- **WHEN** applying labels\n- **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` SHALL be set to the session ID\n\n#### Scenario: Merge template labels\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template labels\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** template labels SHALL be merged with system labels\n- AND system labels SHALL not be overridden by template labels\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Annotation application\n\nThe system SHALL apply required annotations to sandbox pods.\n\n#### Scenario: Session start annotation\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n- **WHEN** applying annotations\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set to current timestamp in RFC3339 format\n\n#### Scenario: Last activity annotation\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n- **WHEN** applying annotations\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n\n#### Scenario: Auth mode annotation for CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod being created\n- **WHEN** applying annotations\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` SHALL be set to `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode`\n\n#### Scenario: Merge template annotations\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template annotations\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** template annotations SHALL be merged with system annotations\n- AND system annotations SHALL not be overridden by template annotations\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Pod naming convention\n\nThe system SHALL generate unique pod names for sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Pod name format\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `Name=\"my-sandbox\"`\n- **WHEN** generating the pod name\n- **THEN** the pod name SHALL follow format `{sandbox-name}-{randomSuffix}`\n- AND the random suffix SHALL be 5 characters alphanumeric\n\n#### Scenario: Pod name uniqueness\n- **GIVEN** an existing pod with the same sandbox name\n- **WHEN** creating a new sandbox\n- **THEN** the pod name SHALL be unique due to random suffix\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Validation error handling\n\nThe system SHALL validate request parameters and return appropriate errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing name validation\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `Name`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n- AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"name\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing runtimeName validation\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `RuntimeName`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n- AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeName\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid RuntimeKind validation\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n- AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeKind\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime not found\n- **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with non-existent `RuntimeName`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve sandbox pod information.\n\n#### Scenario: Get sandbox by name\n- **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n- AND return `SandboxResponse` for the matching pod\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox not found\n- **GIVEN** a GET request for a non-existent sandbox\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n\n#### Scenario: List sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL list all pods with label selector containing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type`\n- AND return `SandboxListResponse` with all matching pods\n\n#### Scenario: List sandboxes by runtime\n- **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes?runtimeName={runtimeName}`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox deletion\n\nThe system SHALL delete sandbox pods.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name\n- AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox deletion updates session annotation\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n- **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n- AND the pod SHALL be updated before deletion\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Warm pool handling for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL support warm pool management for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Check warm pool availability\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL check for available warm pool pods with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member=true`\n\n#### Scenario: Use warm pool pod\n- **GIVEN** an available warm pool pod exists\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL update the warm pool pod instead of creating a new pod\n- AND remove `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` annotation\n- AND set `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` label\n\n#### Scenario: Warm pool pod not available\n- **GIVEN** no warm pool pod is available\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL create a new pod normally\n\n#### Scenario: Warm pool annotation for new pods\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod created outside warm pool usage\n- **WHEN** the pod is created\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` SHALL NOT be set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Port configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure container ports based on TargetPort definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Add container ports\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `Spec.Ports []TargetPort`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** each `TargetPort` SHALL be mapped to a `corev1.ContainerPort` in the pod spec\n\n#### Scenario: Port name from TargetPort\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name=\"http\"`\n- **WHEN** creating the container port\n- **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.Name` SHALL be set to `\"http\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Port number from TargetPort\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Port=8080`\n- **WHEN** creating the container port\n- **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.ContainerPort` SHALL be set to `8080`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RuntimeClassName handling\n\nThe system SHALL apply RuntimeClassName for sandbox pods.\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeClassName from CodeInterpreter template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName=\" KataContainers\"`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL be set to `\"KataContainers\"`\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeClassName nil handling\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName` nil\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL NOT be set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image configuration for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL configure container image for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Image from template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Image=\"python:3.11\"`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container image SHALL be `\"python:3.11\"`\n\n#### Scenario: ImagePullPolicy from template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullPolicy=\"Always\"`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container `ImagePullPolicy` SHALL be `corev1.PullPolicy(\"Always\")`\n\n#### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets from template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullSecrets`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** `Pod.Spec.ImagePullSecrets` SHALL be set from template\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Environment variables handling\n\nThe system SHALL apply environment variables from template.\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variables from CodeInterpreter template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Environment []corev1.EnvVar`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container `Env` SHALL include all environment variables from template\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variables merge\n- **GIVEN** system environment variables and template environment variables\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** template environment variables SHALL be appended after system environment variables\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Resource requirements handling\n\nThe system SHALL apply resource requirements from template.\n\n#### Scenario: Resources from CodeInterpreter template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Resources` containing limits and requests\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container `Resources` SHALL be set from template\n\n#### Scenario: Default resources when not specified\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Template.Resources`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** default resource limits SHALL NOT be applied (let Kubernetes defaults apply)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Command and Args handling\n\nThe system SHALL apply command and args from template.\n\n#### Scenario: Command from template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Command=[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container `Command` SHALL be set to `[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Args from template\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Args=[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container `Args` SHALL be set to `[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty Command and Args\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Command` and `Args`\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n- **THEN** the container SHALL use the default entrypoint from the image\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session management\n\nThe system SHALL manage session lifecycle annotations.\n\n#### Scenario: Session start timestamp\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for a session\n- **WHEN** the pod is created\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set\n\n#### Scenario: Session timeout calculation\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=15m`\n- **WHEN** calculating session expiration\n- **THEN** the expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + SessionTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: Max session duration calculation\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=8h`\n- **WHEN** calculating maximum session expiration\n- **THEN** the maximum expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + MaxSessionDuration`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling and responses\n\nThe system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors appropriately.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes API error\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns an error\n- **WHEN** processing the sandbox request\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be wrapped in `InternalError`\n- AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"INTERNAL_ERROR\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Pod already exists\n- **GIVEN** a pod with the same name already exists\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 409 Conflict\n- AND `ErrorResponse.Code` SHALL be `\"CONFLICT\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace not found\n- **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n- **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Request context usage\n\nThe system SHALL use request context for API calls.\n\n#### Scenario: Context propagation\n- **GIVEN** an HTTP request with context\n- **WHEN** making Kubernetes API calls\n- **THEN** `r.Context()` SHALL be used as the context parameter\n\n#### Scenario: Context timeout handling\n- **GIVEN** a request context that times out\n- **WHEN** the Kubernetes API call is in progress\n- **THEN** the API call SHALL be cancelled\n- AND response SHALL be HTTP 503 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JSON request parsing\n\nThe system SHALL parse JSON request body correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid JSON parsing\n- **GIVEN** a POST request with valid JSON body\n- **WHEN** parsing the request\n- **THEN** `json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&req)` SHALL be used\n- AND request body SHALL be closed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid JSON parsing\n- **GIVEN** a POST request with invalid JSON body\n- **WHEN** parsing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n- AND `Details.reason` SHALL indicate JSON parsing failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JSON response writing\n\nThe system SHALL write JSON responses correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: Success response\n- **GIVEN** a successful sandbox creation\n- **WHEN** writing the response\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 201 Created\n- AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n- AND body SHALL be `SandboxResponse` JSON\n\n#### Scenario: List response\n- **GIVEN** a successful sandbox list\n- **WHEN** writing the response\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n- AND body SHALL be `SandboxListResponse` JSON\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SandboxHandler.\n\n#### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest validation tests\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Missing name returns 400\n  - Missing runtimeName returns 400\n  - Invalid RuntimeKind returns 400\n  - Valid request passes validation\n\n#### Scenario: Label application tests\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Owner runtime label is applied\n  - Owner kind label is applied\n  - Sandbox type label is correct for AgentRuntime\n  - Sandbox type label is correct for CodeInterpreter\n  - Template labels are merged correctly\n\n#### Scenario: Annotation application tests\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Session start annotation is applied\n  - Last activity annotation is applied\n  - Auth mode annotation is applied for CodeInterpreter\n\n#### Scenario: Pod creation tests\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Pod is created with correct spec from AgentRuntime template\n  - Pod is created with correct spec from CodeInterpreter template\n  - Pod name follows naming convention\n\n#### Scenario: Warm pool tests\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Warm pool pod is reused when available\n  - New pod is created when warm pool not available\n  - Warm pool annotation is removed on reuse\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration tests\n\nThe system SHALL have integration tests with fake Kubernetes clients.\n\n#### Scenario: Full sandbox creation flow\n- **GIVEN** a fake clientset with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n- **WHEN** running integration tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify complete sandbox creation from request to pod creation\n\n#### Scenario: End-to-end API test\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer with SandboxHandler\n- **WHEN** sending POST request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify correct HTTP response and pod creation\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Directory structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize sandbox handler files correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox handler file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `sandbox.go` SHALL exist with `SandboxHandler` implementation\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox handler test file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `sandbox_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | SandboxHandler implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go` | SandboxHandler unit tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod, Container types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, ListOptions, CreateOptions |\n| `encoding/json` | Request/Response JSON handling |\n| `time` | Timestamp handling for annotations |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/api/v1/sandboxes` | POST | Create a new sandbox |\n| `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | GET | Get sandbox by name |\n| `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n| `/api/v1/sandboxes` | GET | List sandboxes |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Invalid request parameter |\n| `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Runtime or sandbox not found |\n| `CONFLICT` | 409 | Pod already exists |\n| `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n| `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Context timeout or dependency unavailable |\n\n---\n\n## Label Keys Applied\n\n| Key | Value Source |\n|-----|--------------|\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `RuntimeName` from request |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `RuntimeKind` from request |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"agent\"` or `\"code-interpreter\"` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | `SessionID` from request |\n\n---\n\n## Annotation Keys Applied\n\n| Key | Value Source |\n|-----|--------------|\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` | Current timestamp RFC3339 |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Current timestamp |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` | `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp (on deletion) |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] SandboxHandler implements Handler interface\n- [ ] POST `/api/v1/sandboxes` creates pods correctly\n- [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` retrieves sandbox info\n- [ ] DELETE `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` deletes sandbox pod\n- [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes` lists all sandboxes\n- [ ] Labels are applied according to shared_types.go constants\n- [ ] Annotations are applied correctly\n- [ ] Warm pool handling works for CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] Port configuration from TargetPort\n- [ ] RuntimeClassName handling\n- [ ] Environment variables from template\n- [ ] Resource requirements from template\n- [ ] Command and Args from template\n- [ ] Validation errors return correct HTTP status\n- [ ] Kubernetes API errors handled correctly\n- [ ] Context propagated to API calls\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":12,"character":34},"end":{"line":12,"character":45}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":40,"character":15},"end":{"line":40,"character":15}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableHealthz"},{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":14},"end":{"line":41,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableReadyz"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843462411,"end":1775843462421}}}}
